commits.message: Removed all music functionality and fixed minor user info bug

issue.title: Add Support For Slash Commands
issue.body: Since Discord is migrating all bots over to slash commands, TDL is falling behind the times. TDL still works with bots that have the "Message Content" privileged intent, and theoretically this shouldn't be an issue for TDL since it's unlikely a TDL-linked Discord bot would be in 100+ servers, however, it'd still be nice to support them.

issue.title: Allow Running Commands Through TDL
issue.body:
For linked accounts, add a command to the Discord bot which would allow you to run commands as your user on the server. As such, we could retain permissions (via LuckPerms), but allow you to run commands even though you're not logged in on the server.

For example, if the `FireControl1847` user was linked to my Discord account, and I had permission on the server to set the weather, then I could run `tdl!run weather clear` or something like that to clear the weather on the server. The command would run through the appropriate permissions check for my user, then if I have permission, it'd run that command on the server

issue.title: Sync LuckPerms Groups with Discord Roles
issue.body:
A really cool feature I want to implement.

To configure, the server owner would associate roles and LuckPerms groups in the config file. Then, for linked accounts, if a user is given one of the linked roles in the Discord server, they'll be given the associated LuckPerms group in the Minecraft server.

I don't think it's intuitive for LuckPerms groups to determine Discord roles, so this feature will likely be a one-way sync from Discord to Minecraft.

issue.title: Dedicated keybind for opening the current shader configuration menu

labels.name: area: user interface
labels.description: The parts that users interact with directly - GUI, configuration, in-chat errors, etc

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
Instead of going to the shaderpack selection screen, then hitting the settings button, I would prefer to hit one key and open the configuration screen for the current shader I'm using.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
I press a button and the config menu opens.

comment.body: +1 on this, similar to how in OptiFine you can press "O" to open the shaderpacks menu
